Grandma Kelly wants to ensure all pre-arrival Village Tasks have reasonable deadlines. She's decided that any task scheduled for 'Before Baby Arrives' should automatically have a due date set to 14 days from creation, giving the village plenty of time to prepare!

Before You Begin
Create a record-triggered automation that automatically sets Due Date for pre-arrival Village Tasks.

Requirements
Trigger Event: Before a Village Task is inserted
Conditions: Support Phase = 'Before Baby Arrives' AND Due Date is blank
Action: Set Due Date to 14 days from today
Examples
Example 1:

Insert: Village Task with Support Phase = 'Before Baby Arrives', no Due Date specified
Result: Task is saved with Due Date = Today + 14 days
Example 2:

Insert: Village Task with Support Phase = 'After Baby Arrives', no Due Date specified
Result: Task is saved with Due Date still blank (no automatic date set)
Example 3:

Insert: Village Task with Support Phase = 'Before Baby Arrives', Due Date = 2025-12-25
Result: Task is saved with the manually specified Due Date (2025-12-25), not overwritten
Example 4:

Insert: 5 Village Tasks in bulk, all with Support Phase = 'Before Baby Arrives' and no Due Date
Result: All 5 tasks get Due Date set to Today + 14 days
Notes
Use a Before Insert trigger to set the field before saving
Use Date.today().addDays(14) in Apex or equivalent in Flow
Only set Due Date if it's currently blank (null)
Do not overwrite manually entered Due Dates
Handle bulk operations properly
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Flow xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>65.0</apiVersion>
    <areMetricsLoggedToDataCloud>false</areMetricsLoggedToDataCloud>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <name>duedate14day</name>
        <dataType>Date</dataType>
        <expression>{!$Flow.CurrentDate} + 14</expression>
    </formulas>
    <interviewLabel>Day 4 -&gt; Auto-Set Task Due Date {!$Flow.CurrentDateTime}</interviewLabel>
    <label>Day 4 -&gt; Auto-Set Task Due Date</label>
    <processMetadataValues>
        <name>BuilderType</name>
        <value>
            <stringValue>LightningFlowBuilder</stringValue>
        </value>
    </processMetadataValues>
    <processMetadataValues>
        <name>CanvasMode</name>
        <value>
            <stringValue>AUTO_LAYOUT_CANVAS</stringValue>
        </value>
    </processMetadataValues>
    <processMetadataValues>
        <name>OriginBuilderType</name>
        <value>
            <stringValue>LightningFlowBuilder</stringValue>
        </value>
    </processMetadataValues>
    <processType>AutoLaunchedFlow</processType>
    <recordUpdates>
        <name>Due_Date_to_14_days_from_today</name>
        <label>Due Date to 14 days from today</label>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <inputAssignments>
            <field>CAMPX__Due_Date__c</field>
            <value>
                <elementReference>duedate14day</elementReference>
            </value>
        </inputAssignments>
        <inputReference>$Record</inputReference>
    </recordUpdates>
    <start>
        <locationX>0</locationX>
        <locationY>0</locationY>
        <connector>
            <targetReference>Due_Date_to_14_days_from_today</targetReference>
        </connector>
        <filterLogic>and</filterLogic>
        <filters>
            <field>CAMPX__Support_Phase__c</field>
            <operator>EqualTo</operator>
            <value>
                <stringValue>Before Baby Arrives</stringValue>
            </value>
        </filters>
        <filters>
            <field>CAMPX__Due_Date__c</field>
            <operator>IsNull</operator>
            <value>
                <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
            </value>
        </filters>
        <object>CAMPX__Village_Task__c</object>
        <recordTriggerType>Create</recordTriggerType>
        <triggerType>RecordAfterSave</triggerType>
    </start>
    <status>Active</status>
</Flow>
